R. L. HALL, Appellant, v. RICHFIELD OIL COMPANY OF CALIFORNIA, and Wm. C. McDuffie, as Receiver for RICHFIELD OIL COMPANY, Appellees. No. 7481. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 21, 1934. James T. Boyle and Franklin W. Peck, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of parties, ordered appeal dismissed, without costs; mandate forthwith.
